Horizontal Pod Autoscaler 

Which is responsible for automatically scalling pods that are running benind service, Before we getinto horizontal pod autoscaler, we need to understand what is 
scaling.
Autoscaling:
============
When traffic increses automaticaly, the resources like CPU and memory has to increase to observe the extra load, This is nothing but scalling the application.
This can be done in couple of ways 
1) we can maintain same number of PODs lets say only two, just incplirease the CPU and memory of the PODs = vertical scaling
2) Instead of increasing CPU and memory of existing PODs, in this case two PODs we can add more PODs  = Horizantal scaling 

How Horizantal pod Auto scaler functions:
=========================================
Metrics Server --> Horizantal Pod Autoscaler --> Deployment --> ReplicaSet --> Pods 
  1) It reads POD metricas from metric Server
  2) If metrics says we need to increase number of PODs, it sents scale instructions to the Deployment
  3) Deployment intrun manages replicasets, Replicaset creates that additional POD
This is How Horizantal pod Autoscaler functionis.

